<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xmi:XMI xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1">
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-jfsEPCyC66MvQTBHtnLOgw" name="Carry out safety assessment of supplier,_4X93YK7REeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-jfsEPCyC66MvQTBHtnLOgw">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
    Safety assessments shall be carried out within each phase on reaching defined milestones. The level of detail of safety&#xD;
    assessments shall depend on the complexity and the ASIL of the item and shall be performed according to ISO26262-2,&#xD;
    6.4.5 and ISO 26262-2, 6.4.6.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
    To understand the relationship between the ASIL level of the item being produced and the independence of the assessor&#xD;
    the user is advised to refer to ISO 26262, vol 8 clause 5.4.5&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-ssj7cIPj36HVHwtaaIVncg" name="Develop DIA,_4X93Ya7REeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-ssj7cIPj36HVHwtaaIVncg">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Development Interface Agreement details how the customer and supplier interact with one another and the information&#xD;
    that is being passed between them. The contents of the DIA must include the appointment of a safety manager on the&#xD;
    customer and the supplier side. they are responsible for the joint tailoring of the safety lifecycle according to ISO&#xD;
    26262 vol 2 clause 5.4.5.1.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The task and activities required to be carried out by both parties&amp;nbsp;along with the work products required to be&#xD;
    exchanged and the persons responsible must also be&amp;nbsp;detailed in the DIA.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Any metrics or target values derived from the targets specified at the systems level (i.e single point and latent fault&#xD;
    metric and probabilities of violation of safety goals also need to be communicated.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is expected that the process and tools used by the customer and supplier should be compatible.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-9duCx1uy3SPYINqqwGPB6A" name="Down select suppliers,_4X93Yq7REeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-9duCx1uy3SPYINqqwGPB6A">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The down selection process is based upon an initial assessment of the tender response to the RFQ. The next stage of&#xD;
    selection is based upon the information relating to the suppliers capability to produce the safety related item to ISO&#xD;
    26262, (this is shown in the optional section here).&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-DkoRXamJ94LeB_idVGwYCw" name="Evaluate Supplier Capabilities,_4X93Y67REeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-DkoRXamJ94LeB_idVGwYCw">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The information required of the suppliers must include details of the suppliers past performance and information&#xD;
    regarding its quality management systems along with confirmation of the suppliers ability concerning functional safety,&#xD;
    results of any previous safety assessments that they have been involved in are also to be taken into account.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    References/recommendations from the development, production, quality and logistics departments of the vehicle&#xD;
    manufacturer as far as they impact functional safety should also be taken up.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-ffQGHCS4iFD3A7HN0gokDw" name="Prepare request for quote (RFQ),_4X93ZK7REeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-ffQGHCS4iFD3A7HN0gokDw">
    <refinedDescription>The customer should provide for the supplier a formal request to comply with ISO 26262, the item definition or functional&#xD;
specification of the item and details relating to the safety goals, functional or technical safety requirements including&#xD;
ASILs if available.</refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-l4d7mP579iJ9UnEGUhWhNg" name="Safety Manager,_4YHoZ67REeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-l4d7mP579iJ9UnEGUhWhNg">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-LtiWQPC8LPkvg2u2Pbkz-A" name="Project Manager,_4YHoa67REeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-LtiWQPC8LPkvg2u2Pbkz-A">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;div style=&quot;MARGIN-LEFT: 2em&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
        Assigns the safety manager&lt;br />&#xD;
        Ensures that the safety activities are performed and compliance with ISO26262 is achieved&lt;br />&#xD;
        Verifies that the organisation has provided the required resources to carry out the functional safety activities&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/div></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-Me8oEVTr37-QwAeynEjfhw" name="Evidence of effective Electrical, Electronic quality management system,_4YHoe67REeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-Me8oEVTr37-QwAeynEjfhw">
    <refinedDescription>All organisations in the development lifecycle of the artifact need to show compliance to a quality management standard&#xD;
such as ISO TS 16949 or IS0 9001 or their equivalents. This is to support the application of ISO 26262</refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-Rd15RkcnE_aIsqJKInLagA" name="Down select suppliers,_B5A6YK7TEeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-Rd15RkcnE_aIsqJKInLagA">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The down selection process is based upon an initial assessment of the tender response to the RFQ. The next stage of&#xD;
    selection is based upon the information relating to the suppliers capability to produce the safety related item to ISO&#xD;
    26262, (this is shown in the optional section here).&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-bABSwZkHEk8sfonY3p3zjQ" name="Develop safety plan,_WdrRQK7TEeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-bABSwZkHEk8sfonY3p3zjQ">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The safety plan is a live set of documents that gets refined throughout the safety lifecycle. Because of this a number&#xD;
    of process and documents become part of the safety plan. The documents required to make up the safety plan are detailed&#xD;
    in the safety planning task. The processes required are outlined in this guidance and point to the various clauses in&#xD;
    the ISO 26262 specification.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The safety manager is responsible for the planing,maintenance and monitoring of&amp;nbsp;the safety activities across the&#xD;
    development subphases in the safety lifecycle.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Safety planning should include information relating to the implementation of strategies, activities and the procedures&#xD;
    required for achieving functional safety.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    This covers the planning for all forms of safety based requirements&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;verification and validation&#xD;
    activities, including general planing for confirmation measures.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The supporting process that are detailed in ISO 26262 Vol 8, such as planning for requirements management,&#xD;
    configuration and change management, interfaces, verification, document templates, the qualification of Software tools,&#xD;
    and hardware and software components.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Detailed guidance is given in ISO 26262 Vol 2, clause 6.4.3.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ProcessDescription xmi:id="-sDivqbRSjaUG9Ux1Ed8fdA" name="Manage supplier interface,_TD4TQZEsEeCUs8vNyweFYw" guid="-sDivqbRSjaUG9Ux1Ed8fdA" version="7.5.1"/>
